76 commissioner to receive compensation of $80 per day for attendance at meetings of
77 the Authority. (NRS 315.977, 315.980) In lieu of this specified amount of
78 compensation, section 22 of this bill requires the Authority to determine the
79 compensation for such attendance in an amount that does not exceed $250 per day.
80 Section 5 of this bill establishes, in addition to the various types of housing
81 services for persons of certain low income that a housing authority may provide,
82 certain powers of the regional housing authority, including authorizing the regional
83 housing authority to enter into a public-private partnership to finance a housing
84 project, construct or operate a housing project for profit and create a nonprofit or
85 for-profit business for the purpose of developing housing projects. Sections 5 and
86 22 of this bill exempt a business entity created by the regional housing authority
87 from the provisions that require that meetings of state and local agencies be open
88 and public.
89 Sections 6, 10, 11, 13 and 16 of this bill revise references to a regional housing
90 authority in existing law to include a regional authority formed pursuant to
91 section 3.
92 Section 8 of this bill indicates the placement of sections 2-5 in existing law
93 relating to housing authorities.
94 Section 9 of this bill applies the definitions in existing law and section 2 to the
95 provisions of sections 2-5.
96 Section 15 of this bill indicates the powers of a housing authority to carry out
97 and effectuate the purposes and provisions of existing law relating to housing
98 authorities includes the provisions of sections 2-5.
99 Section 25 of this bill repeals obsolete provisions relating to the provision of
100 housing by a housing authority. Section 7 of this bill makes conforming changes to
101 eliminate references to the repealed provisions.
